Third-party protocols (interoperated with, not included)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
cardo is a user interface. It composes calls to third-party Solana programs via
their public on-chain interfaces (program IDs, instruction/account layouts, and
— for some — public HTTP APIs). It does NOT contain, fork, or redistribute the
source of any of these protocols; each remains the property of its authors and
is governed by its own license and trademarks:

  Meteora (DAMM, DLMM, vaults) · Raydium (AMM, CLMM, CPMM) · Orca (Whirlpool) ·
  Marinade · Mango · Kamino · Drift · Jupiter · Phoenix · Pump.fun / PumpSwap ·
  Streamflow · Realms / SPL Governance · Squads · Jito · Wormhole · Circle CCTP ·
  SPL stake-pool / JitoSOL.

Program IDs and related on-chain metadata are sourced from the public
@rome-protocol/registry package.

